e so=\r\nmething or someone beautiful and the enemy of &quot;desire&quot; (one of shadripus - =\r\nsix internal enemies) tries to attack your mind. Or suppose someone abuses =\r\nyou and the enemy of &quot;anger&quot; tries to attack your mind. How does your mind =\r\nfight back?\n\nJust as you need energy to fight external enemies, your mind n=\r\needs energy to fight internal enemies. If your mind has no shakti, the enem=\r\nies take over and take mind in a direction. If you mind has and exerts shak=\r\nti, the enemies are stopped (fully or partially) and the their push on the =\r\nmind is negated.\n\nWhen you eat, you get physical energy. When you exercise,=\r\n that physical energy is stored in the right places of the body. Similarly,=\r\n when your mind spends time in a state of focused calmness, it eats from th=\r\ne universal source of shakti and gets nourished. When it spends time in pat=\r\nterns of regulated exercises (e.g. homam, japam, bhajan, satsang etc), it s=\r\ntores that shakti in the right places in the mind.\n\nJust as physical energy=\r\n helps you fight external enemies who attack you, this spiritual energy hel=\r\nps you fight internal enemies who attack you.\n\nIf your surrender is perfect=\r\n and you are going through the good and bad fruits of your karmas without c=\r\nommitting new karmas, your point is right. You are like a weightless leaf a=\r\nnd you need no energy - you go with the flow. But, if you still have a cond=\r\nitioned mind that is vulnerable to attacks from shadripus and vulnerable to=\r\n committing NEW karmas, don&#39;t you think some energy is needed?\n\nDon&#39;t look =\r\nat spiritual shakti as something that enables you to do great deeds in the =\r\nworld. Though that too is possible, that is a ego-promiting attitude and in=\r\nappropriate for most sadhakas. Looks at spiritual shakti as something that =\r\nenables you to fight back your own internal enemies and overcome your own w=\r\neaknesses.\n\n* * *\n\n4. If you are living every second without any goals/agen=\r\ndas/ wishes/anticipat ions at all, then you are all already liberated and t=\r\nhen your point is meaningful.\n\nBut, if you do have some some goals, some wi=\r\nshes, some anticipations, some agendas etc, then you should realize that th=\r\nose wishes and anticipations have a kinetic energy of their own (kaarmicall=\r\ny) and they bind you further. You need the spiritual energy (shakti) accumu=\r\nlated through exertion of self-control to negate that kinetic energy and st=\r\nop you from getting bound further.\n\nSome people make the mistake of thinkin=\r\ng that desire of moksha is also a desire and can stop you from moksha. That=\r\n is true. However, it is better than many other desires and definitely wort=\r\nh having. It can be jettisoned when the time comes.\n\nSuppose you have a tra=\r\nsh can in which you collect trash. Just throw away the collected trash and =\r\nhang on to the trash can. If you throw away the can too, then new trash tha=\r\nt comes in will be all over the floor. So keep the can so that you keep col=\r\nlecting trash and throwing it away. You can throw away the trash can also, =\r\nwhen you are absolutely sure that no trash is being generated.\n\nBest regard=\r\ns,\nNarasimha\n------------ --------- --------- --------- --------- ---------=\r\n -\nFree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It Yo=\r\nurself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana:\nhttp://www.VedicA=\r\nst rologer.org\nFilms that make a difference: http://SaraswatiFil ms.org\nSpi=\r\nrituality: http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/vedic- wisdom\nJyotish writings: =\r\nhttp://groups. yahoo.com/ group/JyotishWri tings\n------------ --------- ---=\r\n------ --------- --------- --------- -\n\n&gt; Date: Thu, 4 Mar 2010 11:42:03 +0=\r\n000\n&gt; Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Brahmacharya and Sadhana\n&gt; From: Manish P=\r\nandit &lt;mm.pandit@gmail. com&gt;\n&gt; To: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pv